SIMPLE: mocha
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mocha
<hw>Mo"cha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A seaport
town of Yemen, on the Red Sea, also spelled <asp>Mukha</asp>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A variety of coffee originally brought from
Mocha.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An Abyssinian weight, equivalent to a Troy
grain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A flavoring made from an infusion of coffee or of a
combination of coffee with chocolate or cocoa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A color of a deep chocolate brown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mocha stone</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>moss
agate.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moche</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
